## What PHIPA covers

PHIPA (Personal Health Information Protection Act, 2004, S.O. 2004, c. 3,
Sched. A) is Ontario's health-sector privacy statute. It governs the
collection, use, and disclosure of personal health information (PHI) by
HICs and their Agents.

Authoritative text: <https://www.ontario.ca/laws/statute/04p03>
(accessed 2026-05-12).

IPC's guidance and resources for HICs:
<https://www.ipc.on.ca/en/health-organizations> (accessed 2026-05-12).

